            'description' => '<p><b>Siger of Brabant</b> (<i>Sigerus</i>, <i>Sighier</i>, <i>Sigieri</i> or <i>Sygerius de Brabantia</i>; c. 1240 – before 10 November 1284) was a 13th-century philosopher from the southern Low Countries who was an important proponent of Averroism. He was considered a radical by the conservative members of the Roman Catholic Church, but it is suggested that he played as important a role as his contemporary Thomas Aquinas in the shaping of Western attitudes towards faith and reason.</p>',
