                'intro' => 'French philosopher',
            'description' => '<p><b>Nicole Oresme</b> (<small>French: </small><span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)">[nikɔl ɔʁɛm]</span>; c. 1320–1325 – July 11, 1382), also known as <b>Nicolas Oresme</b>, <b>Nicholas Oresme</b>, or <b>Nicolas d\'Oresme</b>, was a significant philosopher of the later Middle Ages. He wrote influential works on economics, mathematics, physics, astrology and astronomy, philosophy, and theology; was Bishop of Lisieux, a translator, a counselor of King Charles V of France, and probably one of the most original thinkers of 14th-century Europe.</p>',
