                    'intro' => 'German philosopher',
                'description' => '<p><b>Ernst Alfred Cassirer</b> (<span></span>; <small>German: </small><span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)">[ˈʔɛɐ̯nst kaˈsiːʁɐ]</span>; July 28, 1874 – April 13, 1945) was a German philosopher. Trained within the Neo-Kantian Marburg School, he initially followed his mentor Hermann Cohen in attempting to supply an idealistic philosophy of science.
