                'qid' => 'Q964199',
                'intro' => 'Tibetan Buddhist monk and scholar',
            'description' => '<p><b>Gyaltsab Je</b> (Tibetan: <span lang="bo">རྒྱལ་ཚབ་རྗེ་</span>, Wylie: <i>Rgyal tshab rje</i>) (1364–1432) or more elaborately, Gyaltsab Dharma Rinchen was born in the Tsang province of central Tibet. He was a famous student of Je Tsongkhapa, and actually became the first Ganden Tripa (throne holder) of the Gelug tradition after Je Tsongkhapa\'s death. He also studied with Rendawa Zhonnu Lodro (red mda\' ba gzhon nu blo gros, 1349-1412).
