                'intro' => 'Italian author',
            'description' => '<p><b>Moderata Fonte</b>, pseudonym of <b>Modesta di Pozzo di Forzi</b> (or <b>Zorzi</b>), also known as <b>Modesto Pozzo</b> (or <b>Modesta</b>, feminization of Modesto),  (1555–1592) was a Venetian writer and poet.  Besides the posthumously-published dialogues, <i>Giustizia delle donne</i> and <i>Il merito delle donne</i> (gathered in <i>The Worth of Women</i>, 1600) for which she is best known, she wrote a romance and religious poetry. Details of her life are known from the biography by Giovanni Niccolò Doglioni (1548-1629), her uncle, included as a preface to the dialogue.</p>',
