        'description' => '<p><b>Bertha Felicitas Sophie Freifrau von Suttner</b> (Baroness <b>Bertha von Suttner</b>, <small>pronounced </small><span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)">[ˈbɛɐ̯ta fɔn ˈzʊtnɐ]</span>, née Countess Kinsky, Gräfin Kinsky von Wchinitz und Tettau; 9 June 1843 – 21 June 1914) was an Austrian-Bohemian pacifist and novelist. In 1905 she became the second female Nobel laureate (after Marie Curie in 1903), the first woman to be awarded the Nobel Peace Prize, and the first Austrian laureate.
